===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# That which resolves uncertainty; anything that answers the question of "what a given entity is".
# Things that are or can be [[know]]n about a given [[topic]]; communicable [[knowledge]] of something. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|I need some more '''information''' about this issue.}}
# The act of [[informing]] or imparting [[knowledge]]; [[notification]]. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|For your '''information''', I did this because I wanted to.}}
# {{lb|en|legal|countable}} A statement of [[criminal]] activity brought before a [[judge]] or [[magistrate]]; in the UK, used to inform a magistrate of an offence and request a [[warrant]]; in the US, an [[accusation]] brought before a judge without a [[grand jury]] indictment. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}
#*'''1968''', Carl B. Cone, ''The English Jacobins'', New York: Charles Scribner's Sons, p. 131:
#*:On May 21, 1792, the Attorney General filed an '''information''' against Paine charging him with seditious libel.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The act of [[informing]] against someone, passing on incriminating knowledge; [[accusation]]. {{defdate|14th|17th c.}}
# {{lb|en|now|_|rare}} The systematic imparting of [[knowledge]]; [[education]], [[training]]. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
# {{lb|en|now|_|rare}} The creation of [[form]]; the imparting of a given quality or characteristic; [[forming]], [[animation]]. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
# {{lb|en|computing|formally}} [&hellip;] the [[meaning]] that a human assigns to [[data]] by means of the known [[conventions]] used in its [[representation]].
# {{lb|en|Christianity}} [[divine|Divine]] [[inspiration]]. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}
# A service provided by [[telephone]] which provides listed telephone numbers of a subscriber. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}
# {{senseid|en|data}} {{lb|en|information theory}} Any [[unambiguous]] [[abstract]] data, the smallest possible unit being the {{ll|en|bit|id=datum}}. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}
# As contrasted with [[data]], information is processed to extract relevant [[data]]. {{defdate|from late 20th c.}}
# {{lb|en|information technology}} Any ordered sequence of symbols (or signals) (that could contain a message). {{defdate|from late 20th c.}}

